{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":488,"text":"So this is James Risen."},{"time":3174,"text":"You may know him as the\nPulitzer Prize-winning reporter"},{"time":5948,"text":"for The New York Times."},{"time":7664,"text":"Long before anybody knew\nEdward Snowden's name,"},{"time":10442,"text":"Risen wrote a book in which\nhe famously exposed"},{"time":13382,"text":"that the NSA was illegally wiretapping\nthe phone calls of Americans."},{"time":17842,"text":"But it's another chapter in that book"},{"time":19636,"text":"that may have an even more lasting impact."},{"time":22405,"text":"In it, he describes a catastrophic\nUS intelligence operation"},{"time":27247,"text":"in which the CIA quite literally\nhanded over blueprints"},{"time":30360,"text":"of a nuclear bomb to Iran."},{"time":32662,"text":"If that sounds crazy, go read it."},{"time":34481,"text":"It's an incredible story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":36456,"text":"But you know who didn't like that chapter?"},{"time":38893,"text":"The US government."},{"time":40592,"text":"For nearly a decade afterwards,"},{"time":42830,"text":"Risen was the subject\nof a US government investigation"},{"time":46107,"text":"in which prosecutors demanded\nthat he testify"},{"time":48500,"text":"against one of his alleged sources."},{"time":50829,"text":"And along the way, he became the face\nfor the US government's recent pattern"},{"time":54928,"text":"of prosecuting whistleblowers\nand spying on journalists."}]},{"cues":[{"time":58681,"text":"You see, under the First Amendment,"},{"time":60373,"text":"the press has the right to publish\nsecret information in the public interest."},{"time":64024,"text":"But it's impossible to exercise that right\nif the media can't also gather that news"},{"time":69182,"text":"and protect the identities\nof the brave men and women"},{"time":72462,"text":"who get it to them."},{"time":74087,"text":"So when the government came knocking,"},{"time":76143,"text":"Risen did what many brave reporters\nhave done before him:"},{"time":79208,"text":"he refused"},{"time":80417,"text":"and said he'd rather go to jail."},{"time":82611,"text":"So from 2007 to 2015,"},{"time":85618,"text":"Risen lived under the specter\nof going to federal prison."}]},{"cues":[{"time":88976,"text":"That is, until just days before the trial,\nwhen a curious thing happened."},{"time":93912,"text":"Suddenly, after years of claiming\nit was vital to their case,"},{"time":97737,"text":"the government dropped their demands\nto Risen altogether."},{"time":100912,"text":"It turns out, in the age\nof electronic surveillance,"},{"time":103484,"text":"there are very few places\nreporters and sources can hide."},{"time":106959,"text":"And instead of trying and failing\nto have Risen testify,"},{"time":110578,"text":"they could have his digital trail\ntestify against him instead."},{"time":114585,"text":"So completely in secret\nand without his consent,"},{"time":117125,"text":"prosecutors got Risen's phone records."},{"time":119903,"text":"They got his email records,\nhis financial and banking information,"},{"time":124443,"text":"his credit reports,"},{"time":126220,"text":"even travel records with a list\nof flights he had taken."},{"time":129808,"text":"And it was among this information that\nthey used to convict Jeffrey Sterling,"},{"time":133617,"text":"Risen's alleged source\nand CIA whistleblower."}]},{"cues":[{"time":138035,"text":"Sadly, this is only one case of many."},{"time":141152,"text":"President Obama ran on a promise\nto protect whistleblowers,"},{"time":144783,"text":"and instead, his Justice Department\nhas prosecuted more"},{"time":148069,"text":"than all other administrations combined."},{"time":151179,"text":"Now, you can see how this\ncould be a problem,"},{"time":153307,"text":"especially because the government\nconsiders so much of what it does secret."},{"time":158758,"text":"Since 9/11, virtually every important\nstory about national security"},{"time":163282,"text":"has been the result of a whistleblower\ncoming to a journalist."},{"time":166670,"text":"So we risk seeing the press\nunable to do their job"},{"time":169592,"text":"that the First Amendment\nis supposed to protect"},{"time":171815,"text":"because of the government's\nexpanded ability to spy on everyone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":175487,"text":"But just as technology has allowed\nthe government"},{"time":177964,"text":"to circumvent reporters' rights,"},{"time":180695,"text":"the press can also use technology"},{"time":182893,"text":"to protect their sources\neven better than before."},{"time":185698,"text":"And they can start from the moment\nthey begin speaking with them,"},{"time":188834,"text":"rather than on the witness stand\nafter the fact."},{"time":192197,"text":"Communications software now exists"},{"time":194313,"text":"that wasn't available\nwhen Risen was writing his book,"},{"time":196869,"text":"and is much more surveillance-resistant\nthan regular emails or phone calls."},{"time":201789,"text":"For example, one such tool is SecureDrop,"},{"time":206031,"text":"an open-source whistleblower\nsubmission system"},{"time":208740,"text":"that was originally created by the late\nInternet luminary Aaron Swartz,"},{"time":212812,"text":"and is now developed\nat the non-profit where I work,"},{"time":215501,"text":"Freedom of the Press Foundation."},{"time":217824,"text":"Instead of sending an email,"},{"time":219500,"text":"you go to a news organization's website,"},{"time":221565,"text":"like this one here on The Washington Post."},{"time":224010,"text":"From there, you can upload a document\nor send information"},{"time":227977,"text":"much like you would\non any other contact form."},{"time":230715,"text":"It'll then be encrypted\nand stored on a server"},{"time":233358,"text":"that only the news organization\nhas access to."},{"time":236351,"text":"So the government can no longer\nsecretly demand the information,"},{"time":239748,"text":"and much of the information\nthey would demand"},{"time":241876,"text":"wouldn't be available in the first place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":244475,"text":"SecureDrop, though, is really\nonly a small part of the puzzle"},{"time":247463,"text":"for protecting press freedom\nin the 21st century."},{"time":251035,"text":"Unfortunately, governments\nall over the world"},{"time":253432,"text":"are constantly developing\nnew spying techniques"},{"time":255956,"text":"that put us all at risk."},{"time":258043,"text":"And it's up to us going forward\nto make sure"},{"time":260765,"text":"that it's not just\nthe tech-savvy whistleblowers,"},{"time":263289,"text":"like Edward Snowden, who have\nan avenue for exposing wrongdoing."},{"time":267408,"text":"It's just as vital that we protect the\nnext veteran's health care whistleblower"},{"time":272179,"text":"alerting us to overcrowded hospitals,"},{"time":275511,"text":"or the next environmental worker"},{"time":277862,"text":"sounding the alarm\nabout Flint's dirty water,"},{"time":281084,"text":"or a Wall Street insider"},{"time":282788,"text":"warning us of the next financial crisis."},{"time":285869,"text":"After all, these tools weren't just built\nto help the brave men and women"},{"time":290021,"text":"who expose crimes,"},{"time":291583,"text":"but are meant to protect\nall of our rights under the Constitution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":295460,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":296635,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}